<title>SINGAPORE: Creative shares surge 27.7 percent.</title>
<headline>Creative shares surge 27.7 percent.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1996-09-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Creative Technologies shares surged 27.7 percent, or S$1.65, to S$7.65 at mid-morning on Tuesday as a major research house upgraded the stock to a &quot;hold&quot; from a &quot;sell&quot;, dealers said.  </p>
<p>The stock was last traded at Singapore $7.70 on volume of 403,300 shares.</p>
<p>Dealers said Merrill Lynch had upgraded its recommendation for the computer firm saying that the company was &quot;getting their act together&quot;.</p>
<p>The research house also doubled its 1997 full year earnings forecast for Creative to a profit of US$24.6 million.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, other research companies contacted said they had not adjusted their earning projections for Creative and some still expect the company posting losses for 1997.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703083)</p>
